## Methodology

This project follows the **Agilar Agentic Coding methodology** (`agilar-coder`). The terms "methodology", "method", and "framework" all refer to the same thing: the Agilar Agentic Coding methodology.

### Core Principles

1. **Human Designs, AI Executes** — The human is always the Product Owner. The AI is a skilled developer. Humans make decisions, AI follows process rigorously.
2. **Working Agreements** — Non-negotiable quality gates (see below). Not guidelines — commitments the team enforces.
3. **Opinionated by Default** — Concrete choices, not open-ended guidance. Start with defaults, adapt only when needed.

### Development Lifecycle

Every piece of work follows this lifecycle (scale ceremony to complexity, but the default is all steps):

1. **Capture** — Create a PBI before starting any work (PBI-first rule)
2. **Refine** — Write acceptance criteria, explore approaches, get design approval
3. **Plan** — Break into ordered, testable implementation tasks
4. **Implement** — Execute with TDD (red-green-refactor per task)
5. **Review** — Code review for spec compliance and quality
6. **Verify** — Run full test suite, prove acceptance criteria met with fresh evidence
7. **Finish** — Merge, clean up branches/worktrees
8. **Deploy** — Ship to production, verify health
9. **Close** — Mark done, update CHANGELOG, suggest version bump

Shortcuts exist for simple work (bug fixes, config changes, research) — the scrum-master skill guides when steps can be skipped.

