## Versioning

This project uses [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/) (`major.minor.patch`).

- **VERSION** file at project root — source of truth
- **CHANGELOG.md** — documents what changed per version ([Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format)

Version impact classification:
- **Major** — breaking changes (API changes, removed features, changed behavior that affects consumers)
- **Minor** — new features, new capabilities (backwards-compatible)
- **Patch** — bug fixes, documentation, refactoring (no behavior change)

The agent classifies version impact during PBI design, suggests a bump at completion, and the human confirms.

## Filesystem Backlog

PBI files live in `backlog/` and move through folders as they progress:

| Folder | Status | Contains |
|--------|--------|----------|
| `backlog/` | Backlog | Unrefined PBI files |
| `backlog/ready/` | Ready | Refined + planned PBIs, queued for execution |
| `backlog/in_progress/` | In Progress | PBIs currently being worked on |
| `backlog/done/` | Done | Completed PBIs (archive) |

**Execute ready PBIs:**
- "Build the next ready PBI" — picks oldest from ready/, executes, archives to done/
- "Build all ready PBIs" — processes the queue

{{#if EXTERNAL_BACKLOG}}**Sync:** {{BACKLOG_TOOL}} is the primary source of truth. The filesystem is a parallel record. Agent edits files first, then syncs. Inconsistencies trigger a warning.{{/if}}

